docs.text: set in the wild west , this carry on centres around the arrival of the rumpo kid ( sidney james ) and his cronies in stodge city .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: his dodgy dealings and summary shootings aggravate judge burke ( kenneth williams ) so much that he asks sheriff albert earp ( jon pertwee ) to drive rumpo out of town .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: instead , the rumpo kid shoots the sheriff dead .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: therefore , judge burke sends for a law marshall to come in and clean up the city .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: due to a misunderstanding , an english sanitary engineer called marshall p . knutt ( jim dale ) is assigned , without knowing it , as the law marshall for stodge city .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he arrives at the same time as annie oakley ( angela douglas ) who is seeking revenge for her father , the sheriff's murder .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when marshall arrives at stodge city , he soon becomes aware of the misunderstanding and due to his rather limited intellect , he is manipulated by the rumpo kid and always ends up getting things wrong .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in the end , there is a head-to-head between rumpo and marshall .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: with the rumpo's past experience , it would seem that marshall is out of his depth , but using his sanitary skills and learning the ways of the west from annie oakley , he at least stands some chance !
docs.label: positive

docs.text: sid james , with an american accent , is perfect as the rumpo kid , a part which suits him down to the ground .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: jim dale provides one of his best carry on performances as the stupid sanitary engineer , and angela douglas is very effective in her role as the revengeful daughter .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: other regulars that appear in this movie include charles hawtrey and bernard bresslaw ( in his debut ) as big heap and little heap respectively .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: big heap is the local indian leader and the crazy casting of hawtrey for this part is very amusing , as is his performance : - he steals every scene he is in even though he does not enter the film until thirty minutes past .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: joan sims provides useful and amusing support as belle , the local bar owner who takes a fancy to the rumpo kid .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however , the part of doc played by peter butterworth and sheriff albert earp played by jon pertwee are not really necessary , and pertwee's performance is rather poor .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: kenneth williams uses a new voice but struggles with the weak part of the 'judge' .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: even so , this carry on was sid james and kenneth williams' favourite .
